title: neat receipts full version v3 sp1
description:
These lazy people at Neatco won&#039;t release 64-bit installers for their software, and they force you to stick a serial number in to download the installer if you lose the CD.  Insult to injury, the serial key you get on your CD isn&#039;t validated against their database if you bought from Woot.  So, this is the karmic wheel turning.

Neat Receipts CD, v3, full

It will NOT install on a 64-bit OS.  You are welcome to try, and encouraged to tear it up and rebuild it for a 64-bit install.

Good luck, hope this helps someone.
